Upon Wedneſday the 7th. of this inſtant January many Gentlemen and Eminent Citizens, who had been concerned for managing the Petition for the Sitting of the Parliament, upon the 26th. inſtant met together and agreed upon the method of finiſhing the ſame, and of nominating Fit perſons for the preſenting it to His Majeſtie, which being accordinglie done; theſe Gentlemen following (viz.)


Sir Gilbert Gerrard Barronet, Son in Law to the late Biſhop of Durham.

Francis Charlton Eſq;

John Ellis Eſq;

John Smith Eſq;

Johnſon of Stepney Eſq;

Ellis Criſpe Eſq;

Anthony Selby Eſq;

Henry Aſhurſt Eſq;

Tho. Smith Eſq;
